text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!LanguageOfTheNacirema]]%0a%0a!Philosophy Lessons from BLOW%0a%0a:Author: chester_g%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aThe analyzation of BLOW in the Nacirema Culture%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aThe Nacireman have a complicated relationship with the word BLOW. An explosion of anger is when someone BLOWs up, but when told something shocking they often BLOW their own mind. In rage someone may tell another to “BLOW me” when annoyed, but in a moment of sexual attraction say the very same thing. A busy person might get too stressed and want to BLOW off steam, while a lazy friend may BLOW you off to sit at home instead of hanging out with you. All these definitions make a person want to exchange BLOWS with the originators of the English language, or completely BLOW by them as they run away. %0a%0aThis complicated relationship is similar to the Nacireman word FUCK, in the importance that emotional relevance has on a word. Whether it is anger, fear, or love, emotion tends to drive the way we speak very often. These emotions may cause drastic reactions, whether impulsive or instinctive to a person’s true nature. The Nacireman people in moments of high pressure where these emotions may be stronger than others, a noticeable difference can be seen in actions and decision making ability. Thus this drastic difference results in many different meanings to a seemingly peaceful verb that is commonly in reference to the wind. %0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a#foxbegin 210507-230824-908630#%0a(:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a!!!Additional insight into the Nacirema through the word "BLOW" %0a-> - janet_b%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0aThe culture of the Nacirema seems to be both steeped in sexuality, while simultaneously shunning it. These people seem to constantly be balancing on the knife's edge of referencing sex while never overtly mentioning it, or when they do so, it is in a negative context. "Blow", like "fuck", are seen as either explicitly violent or sexual. The fact that a euphemism for such a bodily function is so frequently compared to an act of aggression displays an underlying concept of an inherent power imbalance between people that may be doing sexual acts.%0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 210507-230824-908630#%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: B:)%0a(:Category: LanguageOfTheNacirema:)
